headline: Why Goldman Stands Out as a Trump-Era Winner on Wall Street
summary: Donald Trump’s  election has unleashed big hopes in the market for dealmaking, regulatory easing and private credit.  Goldman is the top-performer among global banks in the S&P 500 so far in November, up nearly 15%.  Like other Wall Street banks, Goldman would benefit from an uptick in merger-and-acquisition or initial-public-offering activity, as well as any regulatory rollback.
